case_body_condition: Not recognizable - Near complete or complete skeleton
case_circumstances: On 05-15-1935 the skeletol remains of three persons were found off of an old logging road in East Middlebury, Vermont. The location has recently been identified as off of Burnham Drive, a road that did not exist at the time. The three skeletons found together were of a female age 35 to 45, a juvenile teen age 13 to 15 and a child age 9 to 11.
